{% comment %} angle-testimonials.liquid — categorised testimonials, carousel per tab {% endcomment %}

{%- liquid
  assign eyebrow = section.settings.eyebrow | default: 'Real results'
  assign heading = section.settings.heading | default: 'What people are saying.'
-%}

<section class="at-wrap" data-section-id="{{ section.id }}">
  <div class="at-inner">

    <header class="at-head">
      <div class="at-head__rule" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <p class="at-head__eyebrow">{{ eyebrow }}</p>
      <h2 class="at-head__heading">{{ heading }}</h2>
    </header>

    <!-- Category tabs -->
    <div class="at-tabs" role="tablist" aria-label="Review categories">
      <button class="at-tab is-active" role="tab" aria-selected="true"  data-tab="sleep"          aria-controls="at-panel-sleep">Sleep</button>
      <button class="at-tab"           role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="womens-health"  aria-controls="at-panel-womens-health">Women's Health</button>
      <button class="at-tab"           role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="stress"         aria-controls="at-panel-stress">Stress</button>
      <button class="at-tab"           role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="anxiety"        aria-controls="at-panel-anxiety">Anxiety</button>
      <button class="at-tab"           role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="fitness"        aria-controls="at-panel-fitness">Fitness</button>
      <button class="at-tab"           role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="recovery"       aria-controls="at-panel-recovery">Recovery</button>
    </div>

    <!-- Panels -->
    <div class="at-panels">

      <!-- SLEEP -->
      <div class="at-panel is-active" id="at-panel-sleep" role="tabpanel" data-panel="sleep">
        <div class="at-carousel">
          <div class="at-track">

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">I finally know why I'm tired.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">I used to think eight hours was eight hours. The ring showed me I was getting maybe forty minutes of deep sleep on a good night. Changed my whole evening routine — no screens after nine, no alcohol. Deep sleep went from 42 minutes to over an hour in three weeks.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Jess M.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Wore it for 6 weeks</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">My sleep score is the first thing I check.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">Before this I had no idea if I was sleeping well or just lying in bed long enough. Now I can see exactly how much REM I get and when my sleep quality drops. Figured out that late coffee is ruining my deep sleep. Small change, big difference.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Daniel K.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Caught my sleep apnea before my doctor did.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">The SpO₂ readings kept dipping to 91–92% and I had no idea why. Brought the data to my GP, she ordered a sleep study, and sure enough — mild sleep apnea. I had no symptoms I could identify myself. The ring flagged it first.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Brian T.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Shifted my sleep window, changed my life.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">Data showed my best deep sleep happened between 11pm and 3am — I was going to bed at 1am and missing half of it. Moved bedtime earlier by 90 minutes. My morning readiness scores jumped by about 15 points on average. I feel like a different person.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Natalie R.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Wore it for 3 months</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Tracked jet lag recovery for the first time.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">I fly from the US to Japan for work every quarter. Used to just white-knuckle through the first few days. Now I can see exactly when my body has adjusted — usually day four. I time my meetings accordingly. The data gave me an edge I didn't know I needed.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Marcus W.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Frequent traveler</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">My husband laughs at how obsessed I am.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">Every morning I'm comparing last night's score to the week's average. The sleep staging is detailed enough to be useful and simple enough to understand. I've recommended it to everyone I know who complains about being tired.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Priya L.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

          </div>
          <div class="at-nav">
            <button class="at-nav__btn at-nav__btn--prev" aria-label="Previous review">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" width="18" height="18"><polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="at-dots"></div>
            <button class="at-nav__btn at-nav__btn--next" aria-label="Next review">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" width="18" height="18"><polyline points="9 6 15 12 9 18"/></svg>
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- WOMEN'S HEALTH -->
      <div class="at-panel" id="at-panel-womens-health" role="tabpanel" data-panel="womens-health" hidden>
        <div class="at-carousel">
          <div class="at-track">

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">I can see my cycle in the data.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">My basal temp shifts confirm my luteal phase every single time. I no longer track my period by counting days — I track it by temperature. The spike is consistent within 0.2°C and happens 24–48 hours after ovulation. First time I've had objective data on my own body.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Claire B.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">The ring caught something my OB didn't.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">My temp readings sat 0.4°C above baseline for three weeks straight. On a hunch I called my doctor. Low-grade infection I hadn't felt at all. Continuous monitoring caught a deviation that a one-off appointment would have missed entirely. I'll never not wear this now.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Rachel S.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Perimenopause, finally made legible.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">I'm 47 and my sleep has been unpredictable for two years. Having data on exactly when I wake up, how fragmented my sleep is, and whether it correlates with temperature spikes has helped me have much more specific conversations with my gynecologist. It gave me language for what I was experiencing.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Diane W.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Wore it 5 months</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">I finally understand my energy fluctuations.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">Some weeks I feel unstoppable, others I can barely get off the couch. The ring showed me the pattern — my readiness scores follow my cycle almost perfectly. Low energy in the luteal phase isn't laziness, it's physiology. The data made me stop fighting my body and start working with it.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Maya K.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Better than any period tracking app I've tried.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">I've used Clue, Natural Cycles, and Ovia. All of them rely on me inputting data. This ring collects it passively — I can see my actual basal temp trend without a thermometer every morning. For fertility awareness it's the most accurate passive tool I've ever used.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Hannah F.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Tracked my sleep through postpartum.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">Wore it through my third trimester and the first four months after delivery. Being able to show my midwife actual sleep data — not just "I'm exhausted" — meant she took my sleep deprivation seriously. We discussed it as a health issue, not a lifestyle inconvenience. Postpartum care needs more data like this.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Zoe A.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">New mom</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

          </div>
          <div class="at-nav">
            <button class="at-nav__btn at-nav__btn--prev" aria-label="Previous review">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" width="18" height="18"><polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="at-dots"></div>
            <button class="at-nav__btn at-nav__btn--next" aria-label="Next review">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" width="18" height="18"><polyline points="9 6 15 12 9 18"/></svg>
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- STRESS -->
      <div class="at-panel" id="at-panel-stress" role="tabpanel" data-panel="stress" hidden>
        <div class="at-carousel">
          <div class="at-track">

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">HRV doesn't lie about stress.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">My HRV tanks during deadline weeks even when I think I'm handling it fine. The ring catches what my conscious mind denies. It's become a way of holding myself accountable — if the number is low I know I need to do something about it, not just say I'm fine.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Noah B.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Works in finance</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Started meditating because of this ring.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">I noticed my readiness scores were consistently low on weekdays despite sleeping the same hours as weekends. The difference was stress. Started doing ten minutes of breathing in the morning and within two weeks my weekday HRV improved noticeably. The data gave me the motivation to actually do it.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Sofia V.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">The ring helped me recognize burnout patterns.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">I'm a teacher and term four is brutal. This year I watched my HRV trend down for three weeks straight before the school holidays. By the time I got the break I was already depleted. Now I have the data ahead of time and I'm managing workload differently. Prevention is better than cure.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Emma T.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">High school teacher</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Used it alongside therapy for anxiety.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">My therapist suggested using objective data alongside our sessions to track how my nervous system was responding to different interventions. The HRV data became a useful conversation starter — we could see which weeks were harder and what was different about them. Data plus therapy is more powerful than either alone.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Charlotte E.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Sleep quality drops before I realize I'm stressed.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">The ring sees stress in my sleep data before I consciously notice it. Fragmented sleep, lower deep sleep percentages, earlier waking — the pattern is consistent. It's become an early warning system for when I need to slow down, which is usually before I think I do.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Isabelle M.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Quantified my stress for the first time.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">I always knew certain situations stressed me out but I couldn't measure it. Now I can. A bad meeting shows up in my heart rate data. A difficult conversation shows up in my overnight HRV. Having numbers attached to stress makes it easier to address and discuss with my doctor.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Ethan J.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

          </div>
          <div class="at-nav">
            <button class="at-nav__btn at-nav__btn--prev" aria-label="Previous review">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" width="18" height="18"><polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="at-dots"></div>
            <button class="at-nav__btn at-nav__btn--next" aria-label="Next review">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" width="18" height="18"><polyline points="9 6 15 12 9 18"/></svg>
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ANXIETY -->
      <div class="at-panel" id="at-panel-anxiety" role="tabpanel" data-panel="anxiety" hidden>
        <div class="at-carousel">
          <div class="at-track">

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">My ring shows anxiety before I feel it.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">My HRV drops 15–20% on the mornings before a panic attack. I've seen the pattern repeat five times now. On low-HRV mornings I cancel anything optional, skip coffee, and leave buffer in my schedule. It doesn't explain why — but it warns me. That's everything.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Mia L.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">First objective view of my nervous system.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">I have generalized anxiety disorder and I've spent years trying to understand what's happening in my body. HRV is the first metric I've found that visibly correlates with my anxiety levels. High-anxiety weeks look different in the data. It's not a cure — it's the most useful tool I've added to my management toolkit.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Jordan P.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Wears it daily</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Breathing exercises actually work. Now I have proof.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">My therapist recommended box breathing for years and I did it inconsistently because I couldn't tell if it worked. The ring showed me that 10 minutes of slow breathing raises my HRV measurably. That evidence was the motivation I needed. Six weeks in, my baseline HRV is up 18%.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Lily T.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">I stopped gaslighting myself about being stressed.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">I used to tell myself I was fine when I wasn't. My HRV told a different story — consistently suppressed during periods I claimed were "under control." Having the data forced honesty, with myself and eventually my therapist. I started a medication review based partly on what the ring showed me over three months.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Alex D.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Helps me tell anxiety from tiredness.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">Both feel the same in the morning — flat, heavy, slow. The ring data helps me distinguish them. Low HRV + low readiness + good sleep = anxiety. Low HRV + low readiness + bad sleep = tired. Different problem, different response. It sounds small but it's changed how I treat myself on hard mornings.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Sadie R.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Data gave me agency over my anxiety.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">Before this I felt like anxiety just happened to me. Now I can see the conditions that precede it — poor sleep two nights running, back-to-back social events, alcohol. The ring doesn't reduce my anxiety directly. It gives me enough signal to intercept it early. That distinction is everything.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Elena V.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

          </div>
          <div class="at-nav">
            <button class="at-nav__btn at-nav__btn--prev" aria-label="Previous review">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" width="18" height="18"><polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="at-dots"></div>
            <button class="at-nav__btn at-nav__btn--next" aria-label="Next review">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" width="18" height="18"><polyline points="9 6 15 12 9 18"/></svg>
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FITNESS -->
      <div class="at-panel" id="at-panel-fitness" role="tabpanel" data-panel="fitness" hidden>
        <div class="at-carousel">
          <div class="at-track">

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">I can actually see my fitness improving.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">My resting heart rate has dropped from 68 to 61 bpm over four months of consistent training. Watching that number trend down week by week is more motivating than any before-and-after photo. Concrete evidence that what I'm doing is working.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Logan P.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Best no-screen workout tracker I've found.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">I lift and run and I don't want to stare at a watch during either. The ring tracks passively and gives me the summary in the app afterward. Heart rate, active time, estimated effort — all there without interrupting my session. Exactly how I want a tracker to work.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Elijah M.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Gym owner</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Swam with it. Surfed with it. Zero problems.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">I'm in the water at least four days a week — ocean swimming and surfing. The ring has been through it all. No fogging, no seal issues, no performance degradation. The ceramic has a couple of micro-scratches from rocks but nothing through the outer layer. Built properly.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Caleb N.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Surfer, 4 months</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Passive tracking is underrated.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">The ring automatically detected when I went for a run and categorized it correctly three out of three times last week without me pressing anything. My Apple Watch needed me to start a workout manually. This just watches and learns. Much less friction.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Harper G.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Tracks what actually matters for performance.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">As a personal trainer I care about three things: resting heart rate trends, HRV, and sleep quality. This ring delivers all three accurately and consistently. I've now recommended it to eleven clients as a more accessible alternative to Whoop. Every one of them is happy with it.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Dominic A.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Personal trainer</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Six days of battery on a fitness ring is wild.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">I charge it Sunday morning while I have coffee. That's it. The whole week covered. I've tried other rings that die after three days. Six days is the number that makes a tracker actually wearable for life.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Isabella R.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

          </div>
          <div class="at-nav">
            <button class="at-nav__btn at-nav__btn--prev" aria-label="Previous review">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" width="18" height="18"><polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="at-dots"></div>
            <button class="at-nav__btn at-nav__btn--next" aria-label="Next review">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" width="18" height="18"><polyline points="9 6 15 12 9 18"/></svg>
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- RECOVERY -->
      <div class="at-panel" id="at-panel-recovery" role="tabpanel" data-panel="recovery" hidden>
        <div class="at-carousel">
          <div class="at-track">

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">Stopped overtraining. Finally.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">I used to train six days a week regardless of how I felt. My HRV was chronically suppressed and I just thought that was normal. The ring showed me it wasn't. Now I take actual rest days when the data says to. My lifts have gone up and I haven't had a nagging injury in four months.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Tyler B.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Powerlifter, 3 months</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
              <div class="at-stars">★★★★★</div>
              <p class="at-card__title">The HRV data is genuinely reliable.</p>
              <p class="at-card__body">I've compared it against my Polar H10 chest strap for three weeks. The trends match consistently even if the exact numbers differ slightly — which is expected from different measurement methods. For day-to-day recovery guidance the ring is more than accurate enough.</p>
              <footer class="at-card__footer">
                <span class="at-card__name">Connor H.</span>
                <span class="at-card__detail">Verified purchase</span>
              </footer>
            </blockquote>

            <blockquote class="at-card">
